A vintage 1960s-style illustration of a frazzled office worker tangled in a massive coiled telephone cord, surrounded by an old rotary desk phone, scattered papers, and a towering stack of instruction manuals. The scene is rendered in muted mustard yellow, avocado green, and burnt orange tones typical of mid-century advertisements. The worker's expression shows comic exasperation, hair slightly disheveled, one hand gripping the phone receiver while the other tugs helplessly at the spiraling cord wrapped around their torso. A retro desk lamp casts dramatic shadows across the cluttered workspace. The aesthetic evokes vintage magazine advertisements with subtle halftone dot textures and warm, nostalgic color palette.
